laboratory_examinations.findings: Mild dependent atelectasis at lung bases; heart mildly enlarged; small axial hiatal hernia; gynecomastia noted; hypodensity along liver dome (10 x 13 mm); hepatic parenchymal hypoattenuation likely due to fatty deposition; gallbladder not fully distended; normal spleen, adrenal glands, pancreas; kidney hyperdense lesion in right upper pole (1.9 x 2.0 cm); hypodense lesion in right renal mid pole (3.2 x 2.6 cm, likely simple cyst); small hypodensity in right renal lower pole (11 x 10 mm); no hydronephrosis; non-obstructing stone in right kidney; tortuous abdominal aorta normal in caliber; no retroperitoneal lymphadenopathy; unremarkable stomach and duodenum; abnormal appendix (12 mm diameter, does not fill with oral contrast) with periappendiceal fat stranding, compatible with acute uncomplicated appendicitis; normal appearance of urinary bladder; phleboliths in pelvis; no pelvic free fluid or lymphadenopathy; no free air or abscess; no suspicious osseous lesions.
